#A62A2A>(1/15/02 3:15:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1122.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A big problem with EQ - Individuality</span><hr size=1> Hi there,<br>
Before I bring up the main point I would like to say I love eq, have enjoyed playing it for well over 4000 hours. I think the VI staff do well.<br>
<br>
To the point, one of the big problems for me in EQ is individuality.<br>
<br>
Lets take 10 lvl 50 wizards. How much do they vary in power, and what they can do? Probably nothing. The variety comes only from the wet wear in their heads.<br>
<br>
It is frustrating that the spell experience for all enchanters is the same, all wizards go through the ice commet age, the lure age etc etc. Its all the same. Appart from how you play your char all characters of a casting class are basicaly equivalent.<br>
<br>
Now of course there is specialization but this does so little . . .<br>
<br>
My first thought was at least this is not true for melee characters, but of course it is. You cannot specialize in a weapon type, there are different fashion statements you can make but in the end most warriors are similar to most other warriors for example.<br>
<br>
Hell a halfling warrior is almost identical in function to a ogre warrior (ignoring slam without shield). There is not even any choice to be a defensive or offensive tank.<br>
<br>
About the only class that has difference is monks. You can choose that nice 10 pound 2hb <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and forgoe alot of ya armor but even that is not a massive difference.<br>
<br>
It would be so wonderful if a wizard could focus on a spell line or type of magic, if a mage could pick a type of pet to be good at, if a warrior could pick a skill and improve in it dramaticaly.<br>
<br>
Oh well idle thoughts. Oh darn, I wonder how much the post 50 specialize options change this argument. Have not gone back to any servers where I am post 50 since fv came out.<br>
<br>
Oh well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just a thought<br>
<br>
Hugs<br>
<br>
Intra <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhueth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hueth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 3:40:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1122.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Individuality</span><hr size=1> I like your idea, ingeneral.  I have had some of the same thoughts before...<br>
<br>
For instance, what if a druid had to choose between improved SOW and Porting?  I think most would choose SOW, but I don't know.<br>
<br>
Maybe a better example is Wizards choosing between Ports or better Nukes..<br>
<br>
I don't have Luclin - but I think the whole alternate advancement thing is tring to hit on the idea.  It's a good idea.<br>
<br>
<br>
Haldrim the Charmer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 3:48:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1122.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Individuality</span><hr size=1> I agree.  I also like the alternate advancement, but I think it doesn't matter too much later on.<br>
<br>
I'd like it if spell schools branched off in neat ways.  If you started down a path and then you were stuck that way.  2 or 3 wizards may stand side by side and be totally different, have different ways of fighting, etc.<br>
<br>
I wish that there were more to becoming a melee too.  I don't think it's very fair that with a little practice a warrior can fight just as well with a piercer as a rogue, who has been using the piercing weapons his whole life.  I think that they should change the way weapon advancement works, so that you can get really high in one weapon but never really high in all weapons.  In that you could learn all weapons equally but you would never be as good with a 2hs as the one that has used that all his life.  In that if you specialize with a 2hs then it becomes nearly (or just) impossible to learn a 1hb more than what you did earlier in life. <p><center><font size=+2><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bmaidensfancy">Shiden Kaidan</a></font>
