<br><i>"Let nothing stand in the way of power."</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moandor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 4:05:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1122.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Individuality</span><hr size=1> Arios, well said! <br>
<br>
I totally agree.  In EQ, there is very little individuality that distinguishes people of the same class or race. <br>
<br>
In fact there is proof that Verant acknowledges this!! <br>
<br>
Look at Shadows of Luclin. They added abilities for higher level (post 50) characters.... this provides a small amount of individuality, as it amounts to some kind of specializations.  <br>
<br>
IMHO..... not enough. And also, why didn't they do this in the first place with characters from the very start at the low levels?  Don't they realize that post-50 characters are a small fraction of their player base? <br>
<br>
