<br>
My advice, if you're looking for customization, is MUDs (*cough* Against the Grain is looking for test players *sneeze*). Even then, some MUD codes are limited, but some allow you to get pretty well customized with levels, such as SW Reality. You just need to find your niche. I like MUDs because it's easier to play a character on them, immortals (imms for short...consider them to be the GMs of the game) actually do provide support and so on. If you're looking for a tight-knit community, play on a MUD. If you're looking for pure roleplaying, MUDs and MUSHs are your best bets, too.  <p>Vall Shadowstrife<BR>
